Review Text: Quality & Taste of the food is quite good. Have ordered Roti, Dal Tadka chatpati, Subz chatpata,Jeera rice and felt that I'm eating home made food. Having said that, I felt the prices of curries can be little reasonable and food can be served with salad.

I've ordered Thali. I'm really not satisfied with the taste. Only the papad is good rest but that comes in very less quantity. Either order from other restaurants if you want to have a North Indian meal. Totally not worth the money.

Great place for vegeterians. Good quality food with good packaging .Try jain thali and other customized thali from wide range of thali they have.also don't miss to try out paner Kadai,rajma, and dal makhani which tastes awesome
And for all the good food, taste and packaging credit goes to the kind and humble owner Mr Gautham
Awesome Veg Biryani. Its taste is unmatched for VEG lovers. The taste enhances if taken along with Mixed Veg Raita. Really making a nice food.
I am new to gachibowli hyd. So was worried about veg food finally tried this place. Very nice food especially thier biryanis are out of the world. Rotis are soft nice quality curries.
Had ordered a maharaja thali and it lived upto its expectations , the prices are in your budget and the food is great , will be there again with bunch of my friends to try out something new from menu

Very nice homely food with nice packaging without charging extra. All briyani are good. Jain briyani is first time I ever ate in hyderabad no onion no garlic but very tasty as regular biryani. So guys give it a try.

Its a big surprise that they claim they prepare good north indian food. They are worst. I ordered executive thali from Anandam. It was very bad. I will never order anything. This place is a total disappointment.
